KONG — STARTUP INSTRUCTIONS

1. Build and start the server (inside Claude Code):

   mvn -q package && setsid java -jar target/kong.jar >server.log 2>&1 </dev/null & disown

2. Start the port-forwarding proxy (PowerShell on Windows host):

   docker run -d --name jira-proxy --network fnba-claude-docker-dist_default -p 7070:7070 alpine/socat tcp-listen:7070,fork,reuseaddr tcp-connect:claude-code:7070

3. Open in browser:

   http://localhost:7070

To stop the proxy:  docker rm -f jira-proxy
To restart it:      re-run step 2
